05/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EU Police Mission chief, Brigadier General Vincenzo Coppola, announced on Wednesday (July 4th) the opening of a temporary field office in Srebrenica, to support security preparations for the July 11th commemoration of the Srebrenica massacre. The office will close on the 13th. As in other years, he said, RS authorities will have overall responsibility for security. An estimated 30,000 people are expected to attend next week's event marking the 12th anniversary of the massacre. 
In other news, the UNDP announced on Wednesday that Tuesday's Srebrenica development conference raised up to 70m euros in pledges. The financing will be earmarked for various infrastructure programmes. (Dnevni Avaz - 05/07/07; RTRS, Srna, PBS BiH - 04/07/07)
